title: Gli Uomini, Che Mascalzoni! (Mario Camerini, 1932)
description:
What Scoundrels Men Are! (Italian: Gli uomini, che mascalzoni!) is a 1932 Italian comedy film directed by Mario Camerini.

The film was a great success, De Sica and Lia Franca became stars and the song Parlami d'amore MariÃƒÂ¹ was a hit. Rarelly in Italian film history, it was filmed on real Milan locations, nowadays it is a sort of documentary how was Milan in the 30s. The film was remade in 1953 by Glauco Pellegrini.
